
<h1>Nearly Full Cases</h1>
<p>
  <%= @order.name %> - <%= @order.note %>
  (closes at <%= l @order.ends.in_time_zone("Pacific Time (US & Canada)"), locale: 'en', format: :long  %>)
</p>
<p>Here is a list of cases that are nearly full.
  Please consider adding another to your order (or adding extra tolerance)
  if you are able to take more without it going to waste.
</p>
<p>
  Note that anything with 'case splittable' may already be full.  The rules for splittable cases are <i>usually</i> as follows:
  24 ct to 12 ct / 25# to 10# /  30 ct to 10 ct  (some exceptions apply)
</p>
<p><%= link_to_ordering(@order, class: 'btn btn-primary btn-large', host: 'food.bowenlift.com', port: false, user: @user) do %>Edit Your Order<% end %></p>
<p>Check the most up to date report here:
  <%= link_to 'Current Case Report', nearly_full_url(@order) %>
<ul>
  <% @order.nearly_full_order_articles.each do |order_article| %>
    <li><strong>need <%= order_article.quantity_left_to_fill_case %> x <%= order_article.article.unit %></strong> (<%= number_to_currency(order_article.article.price) %>) — <%= order_article.article.name %> [<%= order_article.quantity %>..<%= order_article.quantity + order_article.tolerance %>]</li>
  <% end %>
</ul>

<h1>Filled Cases With Extras</h1>
<p>These cases have been filled by people taking more than they want.  Please take some if you need it.</p>
<ul>
  <% @order.full_order_articles.each do |order_article| %>
    <li><strong>extra <%= order_article.extra_amount %> x <%= order_article.article.unit %></strong> (<%= number_to_currency(order_article.article.price) %>) — <%= order_article.article.name %> [<%= order_article.quantity %>..<%= order_article.quantity + order_article.tolerance %>]</li>
  <% end %>
</ul>
<p><%= link_to_ordering(@order, class: 'btn btn-primary btn-large', host: 'food.bowenlift.com', port: false, user: @user) do %>Edit Your Order<% end %></p>